The paper deals with network coding and capacity characterization in wireless relay networks, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) communities. The use of algebraic network coding framework also suggests a potential fit with the algebraic geometry (cs.AG) or algebraic combinatorics (cs.DM) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the Min-cut Max-flow theorem, which is a classic result in graph theory and optimization (cs.DS), and provides sufficiency conditions for achievability, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) applications.
